did you two meet?

217
00:24:16.538 --> 00:24:19.833 line:82%
Three days later.

218
00:24:22.586 --> 00:24:24.838 line:82%
And that moment

219
00:24:25.756 --> 00:24:28.217 line:82%
was priceless.

220
00:24:28.217 --> 00:24:30.177 line:82%
Hurry up.

221
00:24:32.179 --> 00:24:35.474 line:82%
A bus had met with
an accident on the hills.

222
00:24:35.474 --> 00:24:37.476 line:82%
There weren't many casualties.

223
00:24:38.268 --> 00:24:40.646 line:82%
All the passengers were rescued.

224
00:24:41.563 --> 00:24:43.273 line:82%
Only one girl was left.

225
00:24:44.316 --> 00:24:47.528 line:82%
And I got down once again
to rescue her.

226
00:25:18.434 --> 00:25:19.935 line:82%
Pull us up.

227
00:25:25.399 --> 00:25:29.319 line:82%
I'd be lying if I said
I never saw a girl as pretty as her.

228
00:25:30.529 --> 00:25:34.950 line:82%
But I wonder why
I couldn't take my eyes off her.

229
00:25:35.868 --> 00:25:39.747 line:82%
She was looking down.
She was breathing fast.

230
00:25:40.414 --> 00:25:42.374 line:82%
She was petrified.

231
00:25:43.375 --> 00:25:46.670 line:82%
A strand of hair was
getting in her right eye.

232
00:25:47.796 --> 00:25:50.090 line:82%
She was trying to move it,

233
00:25:50.090 --> 00:25:53.802 line:82%
but the winds were strong
and the strand was still there.

234
00:25:54.386 --> 00:25:58.015 line:82%
I moved that strand
of hair from her face

235
00:25:58.432 --> 00:26:00.851 line:82%
and she looked at me nervously.

236
00:26:01.685 --> 00:26:05.731 line:82%
That was the first time
we looked at each other.

237
00:26:06.356 --> 00:26:09.109 line:82%
She kept staring at me in fear.

238
00:26:10.068 --> 00:26:12.571 line:82%
Then, slowly

239
00:26:12.571 --> 00:26:16.241 line:82%
she looked down,
but I kept looking at her.

240
00:26:16.617 --> 00:26:19.495 line:82%
And then, the rope broke.

241
00:26:20.370 --> 00:26:23.957 line:82%
Stop!

242
00:26:23.957 --> 00:26:25.959 line:82%
-Ranjit, stop it!
-What happened!

243
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:27.503 line:82%
Stop!

244
00:26:28.837 --> 00:26:29.963 line:82%
What happened?

245
00:26:29.963 --> 00:26:32.049 line:82%
I've dropped my bag. Please put me down.

246
00:26:32.049 --> 00:26:33.634 line:82%
It's only a bag, ma'am. Let it go.

247
00:26:33.634 --> 00:26:36.762 line:82%
No, I can't let it go.
It's precious to me.

248
00:26:36.762 --> 00:26:38.597 line:82%
Is it more precious than our lives?

249
00:26:38.597 --> 00:26:41.433 line:82%
Yes, it is. Now will you please
take me down or should I go myself?

250
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:43.227 line:82%
Get me down! Now!

251
00:26:43.227 --> 00:26:44.728 line:82%
-Hold on!
-My bag!

252
00:26:44.728 --> 00:26:46.480 line:82%
Stop it!

253
00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:48.524 line:82%
-Ranjit, take us down.
-Veer, have you gone mad!

254
00:26:48.524 --> 00:26:50.901 line:82%
Do as I say! Take us down!

255
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:04.790 line:82%
Here. Ranjit, pull us up.

256
00:27:20.514 --> 00:27:24.226 line:82%
You risked the lives of several
people today just for a bag.

257
00:27:25.352 --> 00:27:27.521 line:82%
What kind of a person are you?!

258
00:27:28.564 --> 00:27:29.982 line:82%
Do you know?

259
00:27:30.232 --> 00:27:33.277 line:82%
We risk our lives every day
to save people's lives.

260
00:27:33.277 --> 00:27:36.655 line:82%
They are strangers.
They are not related to us in any way.

261
00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:41.076 line:82%
Still, when we go home, we feel proud.

262
00:27:41.076 --> 00:27:45.664 line:82%
Since we saved the life of someone's
sister, wife, brother or mother.

263
00:27:45.664 --> 00:27:48.125 line:82%
We gave someone a new life.

264
00:27:48.125 --> 00:27:51.670 line:82%
But today, for the first time
in all these years, I'm doubting myself.

265
00:27:52.671 --> 00:27:53.797 line:82%
For the first time,

266
00:27:53.797 --> 00:27:58.510 line:82%
I feel it's futile risking
my life for someone else's.

267
00:27:58.510 --> 00:28:01.471 line:82%
I'm sorry, ma'am,
but it was disgusting.

268
00:28:09.062 --> 00:28:12.357 line:82%
Get lost!
I don't wish to see your face!

269
00:28:12.357 --> 00:28:15.736 line:82%
Who told you to give Zaara your money!

270
00:28:15.736 --> 00:28:19.489 line:82%
You know I can't refuse Zaara.

271
00:28:19.489 --> 00:28:21.867 line:82%
Even if I did,
she would have snatched it from me.

272
00:28:21.867 --> 00:28:25.329 line:82%
Couldn't you have told me
that she was going to India,

273
00:28:25.329 --> 00:28:27.080 line:82%
not to the local market?!

274
00:28:28.457 --> 00:28:30.876 line:82%
She made me swear on our friendship.

275
00:28:30.876 --> 00:28:34.588 line:82%
You swore on your friendship?
There's a limit to being childish!

276
00:28:34.588 --> 00:28:36.214 line:82%
Who helped her board the bus?

277
00:28:36.214 --> 00:28:38.717 line:82%
Call Akram, immediately!

278
00:28:38.717 --> 00:28:41.219 line:82%
-How could someone be so irresponsible!
-Hello.

279
00:28:41.219 --> 00:28:42.888 line:82%
-Zaara!
-Zaara!

280
00:28:42.888 --> 00:28:44.306 line:82%
Zaara, how are you?

281
00:28:44.306 --> 00:28:45.891 line:82%
-Give it to me!
-Zaara!

282
00:28:45.891 --> 00:28:49.353 line:82%
Mom, I'm fine. Don't worry.

283
00:28:49.353 --> 00:28:51.438 line:82%
What kind of insolence is this, Zaara!

284
00:28:51.438 --> 00:28:54.942 line:82%
Do you know how worried I am here?

285
00:28:54.942 --> 00:28:58.987 line:82%
I was about to inform the police
when this Shabbo told me the truth.

286
00:28:59.571 --> 00:29:04.618 line:82%
-Just come home immediately.
-Mom, the border closes at 4:30.

287
00:29:05.077 --> 00:29:08.038 line:82%
And I haven't even reached Kiratpur yet.

288
00:29:08.038 --> 00:29:13.335 line:82%
Dear Lord! What am I being
punished for? It's almost dusk and...

289
00:29:13.335 --> 00:29:15.087 line:82%
How could you go all by yourself!

290
00:29:15.087 --> 00:29:18.840 line:82%
I promised you that
I'd send the ashes to India.

291
00:29:18.840 --> 00:29:21.259 line:82%
But I made a promise to grandma too

292
00:29:21.259 --> 00:29:23.136 line:82%
that I'd personally take the ashes.

293
00:29:23.136 --> 00:29:25.639 line:82%
Zaara, you're not in Lahore anymore.

294
00:29:25.639 --> 00:29:27.265 line:82%
You're in another country.

295
00:29:27.265 --> 00:29:30.268 line:82%
-Are you crazy?
-I'm really sorry, Mom.

296
00:29:30.268 --> 00:29:36.316 line:82%
But you couldn't understand me
even though I tried.

297
00:29:36.316 --> 00:29:40.529 line:82%
I've never done anything
special in my life, Mom.

298
00:29:40.529 --> 00:29:44.825 line:82%
And I'm not going to do
anything great in my future.

299
00:29:44.825 --> 00:29:47.536 line:82%
My life will also be spent

300
00:29:47.536 --> 00:29:50.664 line:82%
trying to be a good wife
and mother, just like you.

301
00:29:51.707 --> 00:29:55.127 line:82%
But if I do this, I'll be proud

302
00:29:55.127 --> 00:29:58.380 line:82%
that I did something to
help someone's soul rest in peace.

303
00:30:01.842 --> 00:30:06.054 line:82%
Since I've come this far,
I'll return only once I'm done.

304
00:30:07.097 --> 00:30:10.892 line:82%
But if you stay upset with me,
then my journey will be jinxed.

305
00:30:10.892 --> 00:30:14.146 line:82%
Stop this nonsense! A mother
can never jinx her daughter's happiness.

306
00:30:14.146 --> 00:30:15.480 line:82%
I've been crying
for the past eight hours.

307
00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:17.649 line:82%
Don't make me cry anymore.

308
00:30:17.649 --> 00:30:20.152 line:82%
Relax, Mom. I'm cool.

309
00:30:20.152 --> 00:30:23.447 line:82%
Yes, you're cool and we're all fools.

310
00:30:23.447 --> 00:30:26.950 line:82%
If your father returns
before you, then...

311
00:30:26.950 --> 00:30:30.620 line:82%
Don't worry, Mom.
Dad will return next week.

312
00:30:30.620 --> 00:30:33.832 line:82%
-I'll be back by tomorrow. Okay?
-Ma'am, please.

313
00:30:33.832 --> 00:30:36.710 line:82%
Yes. Mom, I'm hanging up.
There's a line behind me.

314
00:30:36.710 --> 00:30:40.005 line:82%
Listen, take care.
And be careful about what you eat.

315
00:30:40.005 --> 00:30:43.341 line:82%
Don't interact with strangers
and do keep calling me.

316
00:30:43.341 --> 00:30:47.721 line:82%
Okay? And don't worry,
my blessings are with you.

317
00:30:47.721 --> 00:30:51.391 line:82%
-Okay, dear. Bye.
-Bye.

318
00:30:51.391 --> 00:30:54.936 line:82%
-How much do I have to pay?
-You were worrying for no reason.

319
00:30:54.936 --> 00:31:00.067 line:82%
Zaara is no less than a boy.
She can have her way anywhere.

320
00:31:00.067 --> 00:31:02.694 line:82%
Thank God, she's all right.

321
00:31:02.694 --> 00:31:06.865 line:82%
This girl almost killed me.

322
00:31:06.865 --> 00:31:08.325 line:82%
Why are you talking to me?

323
00:31:08.325 --> 00:31:10.077 line:82%
I told you to get lost!

324
00:31:10.077 --> 00:31:12.662 line:82%
You say that every time.

325
00:31:12.662 --> 00:31:16.666 line:82%
-We're cool!
-Shut up! To hell with you!

326
00:31:16.666 --> 00:31:20.045 line:82%
Get to work now!
What are you standing here for! Go!

327
00:31:24.591 --> 00:31:27.803 line:82%
Ranjit, my leave has been approved.

328
00:31:27.803 --> 00:31:29.888 line:82%
Mom and dad wanted
me to come home for Lohri.

329
00:31:29.888 --> 00:31:32.099 line:82%
I'll reach faster if
I leave from here in the morning.

330
00:31:32.099 --> 00:31:33.517 line:82%
Negi will accompany you back.

331
00:31:33.517 --> 00:31:36.728 line:82%
-Okay. See you on Monday. Enjoy.
-Thank you. Praise the Lord.

332
00:31:36.728 --> 00:31:40.190 line:82%
Excuse me. Is there a bus here
that goes to Kiratpur?

333
00:31:40.190 --> 00:31:42.067 line:82%
No, there's no bus as of now.

334
00:31:42.067 --> 00:31:44.236 line:82%
There's a bus for
Kiratpur at 7 a.m. tomorrow.

335
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:47.656 line:82%
Is there a hotel around
to spend the night?

336
00:31:47.656 --> 00:31:51.910 line:82%
Hotel? Sure! There's an eatery.

337
00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:53.954 line:82%
That's like a five-star hotel for us.

338
00:31:53.954 --> 00:31:57.207 line:82%
A blanket for 10 rupees
and a bed for 25 rupees.

339
00:31:57.207 --> 00:32:00.669 line:82%
Okay, ma'am,
I'll take your leave. Good night.

340
00:32:42.836 --> 00:32:46.131 line:82%
You risk your lives
to save the lives of strangers.

341
00:32:46.965 --> 00:32:49.301 line:82%
Nothing could be nobler than that.

342
00:32:50.051 --> 00:32:55.223 line:82%
I don't want you to feel
less proud of your job because of me.

343
00:32:55.223 --> 00:32:57.809 line:82%
That's why I'm here
to tell you why I was being stupid.

344
00:32:59.686 --> 00:33:01.980 line:82%
These are my grandmother's ashes.

345
00:33:03.648 --> 00:33:06.026 line:82%
She was Indian.

346
00:33:06.026 --> 00:33:10.405 line:82%
She spent her life serving
my family in Pakistan.

347
00:33:11.072 --> 00:33:15.202 line:82%
She never asked for anything in return.
Just one last wish.

348
00:33:16.494 --> 00:33:19.331 line:82%
She wanted her ashes to be
immersed in the rivers of Kiratput,

349
00:33:19.331 --> 00:33:21.166 line:82%
with her ancestors.

350
00:33:22.918 --> 00:33:25.754 line:82%
This is more precious than my life.

351
00:33:27.255 --> 00:33:30.550 line:82%
Perhaps, you weren't
too keen on saving my life.

352
00:33:30.550 --> 00:33:34.054 line:82%
But I believe that
you must certainly be proud

353
00:33:34.054 --> 00:33:38.350 line:82%
after knowing that you saved
this urn in my bag.

354
00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:44.940 line:82%
Please forgive me if you can.

355
00:33:47.234 --> 00:33:49.027 line:82%
I'm sorry.

356
00:33:56.076 --> 00:33:59.537 line:82%
-Sir, here's your buttermilk.
-Give me.

357
00:34:00.872 --> 00:34:04.125 line:82%
If I had buttermilk in the morning,
I wouldn't be hot-headed.

358
00:34:17.681 --> 00:34:20.725 line:82%
Listen, I have a ticket! Look...

359
00:34:20.725 --> 00:34:23.561 line:82%
Go in. Let them on.

360
00:34:23.561 --> 00:34:26.523 line:82%
-Listen...
-Watch out!

361
00:34:26.523 --> 00:34:28.733 line:82%
Easy... Careful...

362
00:34:28.733 --> 00:34:31.403 line:82%
That's it. No more passengers.

363
00:34:31.403 --> 00:34:34.656 line:82%
-Listen, I have a ticket.
-Everyone has a ticket, ma'am.

364
00:34:34.656 --> 00:34:36.616 line:82%
We believe in first come, first serve.

365
00:34:36.866 --> 00:34:39.327 line:82%
-So, then, where do I sit?
-Go up.

366
00:34:44.916 --> 00:34:47.460 line:82%
Hey! Back off.

367
00:34:47.460 --> 00:34:50.130 line:82%
-Why should I move?
-Why not?

368
00:34:51.089 --> 00:34:54.301 line:82%
Is my wife your sister
that you want to sit with her?

369
00:34:54.301 --> 00:34:56.594 line:82%
Move, or I'll break your teeth.

370
00:34:56.594 --> 00:35:00.932 line:82%
-Please sit. I wasn't aware.
-Hey...

371
00:35:06.187 --> 00:35:08.773 line:82%
You must be wondering why I'm here.

372
00:35:10.859 --> 00:35:14.029 line:82%
Well, do you see that bus over there?

373
00:35:15.155 --> 00:35:17.615 line:82%
Actually,
I should have been on that bus.

374
00:35:17.615 --> 00:35:19.034 line:82%
I was even seated inside.

375
00:35:19.618 --> 00:35:23.455 line:82%
But then, I saw you.
I saw how easily

376
00:35:23.455 --> 00:35:25.415 line:82%
you took this luxurious seat.

377
00:35:27.709 --> 00:35:31.546 line:82%
I thought, either you're brave,
or you're stupid.

378
00:35:32.339 --> 00:35:35.008 line:82%
You've come alone
on such a long journey.

379
00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:38.970 line:82%
Then, I also thought
that I will reach my village

380
00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:43.183 line:82%
but all my life, I'll keep wondering

381
00:35:43.183 --> 00:35:45.518 line:82%
whether that silly girl from Pakistan

382
00:35:45.518 --> 00:35:48.438 line:82%
reached her destination safely or not.

383
00:35:49.397 --> 00:35:52.817 line:82%
So, don't be under the impression
that I'm here to help you.

384
00:35:52.817 --> 00:35:54.486 line:82%
I'm here

385
00:35:55.028 --> 00:35:58.031 line:82%
so that I'm not bothered
by this thought forever.

386
00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.741 line:82%
Thank you.

387
00:35:59.741 --> 00:36:01.993 line:82%
Would you like to have chole?

388
00:36:06.665 --> 00:36:09.250 line:82%
I'm Squadron Leader,
Veer Pratap Singh.

389
00:36:10.251 --> 00:36:12.629 line:82%
I'm Zaara. Zaara Hayat Khan.

