the ashes ritualistically.

450
00:44:05.476 --> 00:44:10.231 line:82%
No, Zaara. You see,
some priests are very strict.

451
00:44:10.231 --> 00:44:11.899 line:82%
Not only will you be humiliated,

452
00:44:11.899 --> 00:44:14.026 line:82%
but I'll be beaten too.

453
00:44:14.026 --> 00:44:15.278 line:82%
Can I ask them?

454
00:44:15.278 --> 00:44:18.072 line:82%
No, you don't go.
Stay here. I'll ask them.

455
00:44:18.072 --> 00:44:20.950 line:82%
Have a seat here, please.

456
00:44:22.869 --> 00:44:26.122 line:82%
The Lord's name is the ultimate.

457
00:44:26.122 --> 00:44:30.418 line:82%
I told you about Kiratpur, right?

458
00:44:30.418 --> 00:44:34.964 line:82%
Immerse my ashes in the rivers
over there. I'll find salvation.

459
00:44:52.899 --> 00:44:54.942 line:82%
-Is your name Zaara?
-Yes.

460
00:44:54.942 --> 00:44:57.486 line:82%
-Are you from Pakistan?
-Yes.

461
00:44:59.030 --> 00:45:03.868 line:82%
I've been serving this
holy place for the past 42 years.

462
00:45:03.868 --> 00:45:06.203 line:82%
I've never seen such
devotion in a person before.

463
00:45:08.039 --> 00:45:12.543 line:82%
Even one's own child wouldn't have done
what you're doing, dear.

464
00:45:12.543 --> 00:45:16.339 line:82%
I'd be fortunate to conduct
prayers for your grandmother.

465
00:45:16.339 --> 00:45:19.967 line:82%
Come with me, dear. Come.

466
00:45:23.930 --> 00:45:27.808 line:82%
Thank you, dear Lord!
You're great.

467
00:45:54.835 --> 00:45:56.587 line:82%
Please come here.

468
00:46:00.758 --> 00:46:02.468 line:82%
What is it now?

469
00:46:02.468 --> 00:46:07.098 line:82%
Bring your hand forward, and fulfill
grandma's last wish along with me.

470
00:46:09.183 --> 00:46:11.143 line:82%
But, how can I...

471
00:46:11.143 --> 00:46:14.855 line:82%
Look, neither am I grandma's
biological child, nor are you.

472
00:46:15.856 --> 00:46:19.777 line:82%
But if it wasn't for you,
I wouldn't have been able

473
00:46:19.777 --> 00:46:21.862 line:82%
to bring grandma's
ashes here so easily.

474
00:46:23.572 --> 00:46:27.451 line:82%
You too have formed
a bond with my grandma now.

475
00:46:27.451 --> 00:46:32.248 line:82%
So, along with me, you have the right
to perform this last ritual too. Come.

476
00:47:05.072 --> 00:47:07.533 line:82%
Zaara, here's your bus ticket.

477
00:47:07.533 --> 00:47:10.911 line:82%
This will take you to Atari,
and then, take a train to Lahore.

478
00:47:10.911 --> 00:47:14.040 line:82%
Here's the change.
Have you finished eating?

479
00:47:15.708 --> 00:47:21.047 line:82%
-Anything else?
-No, thanks. You've already done a lot.

480
00:47:21.047 --> 00:47:25.051 line:82%
I don't know how to thank you.

481
00:47:25.051 --> 00:47:26.635 line:82%
I'm quite frank about all this.

482
00:47:26.635 --> 00:47:28.721 line:82%
If you insist, I'll tell you.

483
00:47:28.721 --> 00:47:32.641 line:82%
Please tell me.
What can I do for you?

484
00:47:32.641 --> 00:47:34.727 line:82%
Think about it.
I'll ask you for it,

485
00:47:34.727 --> 00:47:37.146 line:82%
but you might not be able
to give it to me.

486
00:47:38.272 --> 00:47:41.442 line:82%
You have no idea how
big a favor you've done me.

487
00:47:41.442 --> 00:47:44.904 line:82%
You can ask for whatever you want.
I promise, I'll fulfill it.

488
00:47:46.197 --> 00:47:49.575 line:82%
You're promising without
even knowing what it is.

489
00:47:49.575 --> 00:47:51.869 line:82%
You might repent later.

490
00:47:51.869 --> 00:47:54.580 line:82%
A Pakistani has promised an Indian.

491
00:47:54.580 --> 00:47:57.583 line:82%
This concerns the honor of my country.

492
00:47:57.583 --> 00:47:59.877 line:82%
I can't go back on
my word now even if I want to.

493
00:47:59.877 --> 00:48:02.797 line:82%
Tell me, what can I do for you?

494
00:48:05.883 --> 00:48:07.885 line:82%
Give me another day of your life.

495
00:48:11.097 --> 00:48:15.935 line:82%
-What?
-You brought me close to your life.

496
00:48:17.061 --> 00:48:19.897 line:82%
You made me form a bond
with your grandmother.

497
00:48:19.897 --> 00:48:23.567 line:82%
You've given me a lifelong memory.

498
00:48:26.153 --> 00:48:30.324 line:82%
I want to show you my world
and introduce you to my people.

499
00:48:30.324 --> 00:48:34.912 line:82%
I want to give you
a lifelong memory too.

500
00:48:38.791 --> 00:48:42.378 line:82%
I know this day is
quite precious for you

501
00:48:42.378 --> 00:48:44.713 line:82%
but I promise,

502
00:48:44.713 --> 00:48:47.133 line:82%
you'll never be able
to forget this day.

503
00:48:53.430 --> 00:48:58.519 line:82%
I told you, you'd regret
making that promise.

504
00:49:15.452 --> 00:49:18.372 line:82%
So, you fell in love with her.

505
00:49:21.542 --> 00:49:25.045 line:82%
I still couldn't understand...

506
00:49:27.965 --> 00:49:30.551 line:82%
what was wrong with me.

507
00:49:33.220 --> 00:49:37.600 line:82%
I don't know why I asked
her for another day. I just did.

508
00:49:39.393 --> 00:49:43.522 line:82%
But even then, I knew

509
00:49:43.522 --> 00:49:47.818 line:82%
that our meeting could not end there.

510
00:49:47.818 --> 00:49:52.239 line:82%
We didn't meet to separate eventually.

511
00:49:53.699 --> 00:49:58.495 line:82%
Our relationship was incomplete.

512
00:49:58.495 --> 00:50:01.665 line:82%
There was something left to be done.

513
00:50:04.877 --> 00:50:06.670 line:82%
That's what I thought

514
00:50:06.670 --> 00:50:09.798 line:82%
and hence, I kept saying
what came to mind.

515
00:50:10.591 --> 00:50:13.761 line:82%
And she quietly listened.

516
00:50:16.597 --> 00:50:18.182 line:82%
Did she stay back?

517
00:50:21.477 --> 00:50:23.354 line:82%
Samya...

518
00:50:23.729 --> 00:50:26.857 line:82%
it concerned the honor of your Pakistan.

519
00:50:30.402 --> 00:50:32.655 line:82%
She had to come.

520
00:50:42.331 --> 00:50:46.502 line:82%
Why are you upset?
Did your mom scold you over the phone?

521
00:50:46.502 --> 00:50:51.173 line:82%
-I'm scared of heights!
-Oh! Why didn't you tell me that?

522
00:50:51.674 --> 00:50:54.468 line:82%
You said it was a shortcut.

523
00:50:54.468 --> 00:50:58.055 line:82%
The other route would take us
half the day. I had no choice.

524
00:50:58.055 --> 00:51:02.059 line:82%
So, are you going to be
petrified throughout the journey?

525
00:51:02.059 --> 00:51:04.895 line:82%
Please smile as you're
scaring me with that face.

526
00:51:06.397 --> 00:51:09.817 line:82%
Okay, look. Eat some nuts.
It'll take your mind off it.

527
00:51:10.693 --> 00:51:14.196 line:82%
-Bring your hand forward.
-No.

528
00:51:14.196 --> 00:51:16.532 line:82%
Okay, open your mouth.

529
00:51:20.661 --> 00:51:23.289 line:82%
You want more?

530
00:51:39.138 --> 00:51:41.077 line:82%
Brother Veer is here!

531
00:51:41.167 --> 00:51:44.893 line:82%
Brother Veer is here!
There's a girl with him!

532
00:51:45.311 --> 00:51:49.398 line:82%
Brother Veer is here!
There's a girl with him!

533
00:51:49.398 --> 00:51:53.777 line:82%
Pappu's mother, look,
Veer has brought along his fiancÃ©e.

534
00:51:53.777 --> 00:51:56.905 line:82%
No! His fiancÃ©e
couldn't have come with him.

535
00:51:56.905 --> 00:51:59.116 line:82%
Veer must have married her.

536
00:51:59.116 --> 00:52:01.201 line:82%
She must be his wife.

537
00:52:01.201 --> 00:52:05.998 line:82%
Aunt! Aunt!

538
00:52:07.249 --> 00:52:09.877 line:82%
Aunt!

539
00:52:10.544 --> 00:52:13.172 line:82%
Aunt! Aunt!

540
00:52:16.967 --> 00:52:20.054 line:82%
What is it? What's wrong?

541
00:52:20.054 --> 00:52:22.848 line:82%
-Aunt, Veer is back!
-Veer!

542
00:52:22.848 --> 00:52:26.185 line:82%
Yes, and his wife is with him.

543
00:52:26.185 --> 00:52:31.065 line:82%
That's ridiculous! Veer can never
get married without my permission.

544
00:52:31.065 --> 00:52:35.152 line:82%
I'm telling the truth, Aunt.
The village is out to see him.

545
00:52:39.156 --> 00:52:43.160 line:82%
Fine! Let him come.
I won't talk to him.

546
00:52:45.496 --> 00:52:50.042 line:82%
Chaudhary Sumer Singh!
Listen! Where is he?

547
00:52:59.259 --> 00:53:00.844 line:82%
Behind me!

548
00:53:09.436 --> 00:53:11.522 line:82%
Chaudhary Sumer Singh!

549
00:53:13.315 --> 00:53:15.359 line:82%
Chaudhary Sumer Singh!

550
00:53:16.693 --> 00:53:19.530 line:82%
-Sir, your wife is calling you.
-Yes.

551
00:53:20.489 --> 00:53:21.824 line:82%
She always calls me at the wrong time.

552
00:53:21.824 --> 00:53:24.076 line:82%
Come here, dear.
Let me tell you something.

553
00:53:24.535 --> 00:53:29.289 line:82%
Don't ever get married. If you do,
you'll never do well in sports.

554
00:53:29.540 --> 00:53:31.458 line:82%
-Chaudhary Sumer Singh!
-Okay.

555
00:53:31.458 --> 00:53:34.837 line:82%
Coming... Oh, my wife!

556
00:53:35.337 --> 00:53:37.965 line:82%
I've told you several times not to
disturb me when I'm playing. What is it?

557
00:53:37.965 --> 00:53:42.678 line:82%
I've also told you several
times that you must die on the bed.

558
00:53:42.678 --> 00:53:46.849 line:82%
Why do you want to break
your bones by playing with kids?

559
00:53:46.849 --> 00:53:49.143 line:82%
You know what?

560
00:53:49.143 --> 00:53:52.688 line:82%
No player in this village
can beat Sumer Singh.

561
00:53:52.688 --> 00:53:56.024 line:82%
You have no idea what
a player your son had proved to be.

562
00:53:56.024 --> 00:53:57.609 line:82%
Veer is back!

563
00:53:57.609 --> 00:53:59.486 line:82%
But he's not alone.

564
00:53:59.486 --> 00:54:01.447 line:82%
-Then?
-He's married.

565
00:54:01.447 --> 00:54:03.824 line:82%
Look over there.

566
00:54:04.074 --> 00:54:06.243 line:82%
Come. That's uncle and that's my aunt.

567
00:54:06.243 --> 00:54:08.162 line:82%
Brother Veer!

568
00:54:11.165 --> 00:54:14.293 line:82%
How are you all?

569
00:54:19.923 --> 00:54:21.091 line:82%
-How are you, Kamli?
-I'm fine.

570
00:54:21.091 --> 00:54:23.427 line:82%
Let me go meet dad.
Greetings, Dad.

571
00:54:23.427 --> 00:54:24.803 line:82%
-You idiot!
-What's wrong?

572
00:54:24.803 --> 00:54:27.264 line:82%
You got married without
even asking or informing us!

573
00:54:27.264 --> 00:54:29.266 line:82%
Married... Who got married?

574
00:54:29.266 --> 00:54:31.518 line:82%
-Who's she, then? My wife?
-No...

575
00:54:31.518 --> 00:54:33.353 line:82%
-She's your wife.
-I'll smack you.

576
00:54:33.353 --> 00:54:35.898 line:82%
-Then who's she?
-You're too much, Mom.

577
00:54:35.898 --> 00:54:39.276 line:82%
Can there be only one
relationship between a boy and a girl?

578
00:54:39.276 --> 00:54:42.154 line:82%
Greetings!
She's our guest, Dad.

579
00:54:42.154 --> 00:54:45.657 line:82%
I rescued her and brought her
here to see my village and family.

580
00:54:45.657 --> 00:54:47.618 line:82%
You think she's my wife?

581
00:54:53.790 --> 00:54:56.210 line:82%
The minute I saw her, I knew

582
00:54:56.210 --> 00:55:00.506 line:82%
that this idiot could never get
a girl as beautiful as her.

583
00:55:00.506 --> 00:55:05.052 line:82%
-What's your name, dear?
-Zaara. Zaara Hayat Khan.

584
00:55:05.052 --> 00:55:08.388 line:82%
That's a lovely name.
Where are you from, dear?

585
00:55:08.388 --> 00:55:11.642 line:82%
-Well, from Pakistan.
-There you go! That's amazing!

586
00:55:11.642 --> 00:55:14.520 line:82%
You've become our
extra special guest now.

587
00:55:14.520 --> 00:55:18.065 line:82%
Look, we've always served
the people of our country.

588
00:55:18.065 --> 00:55:20.943 line:82%
This is our first opportunity to serve
someone from the neighboring country.

589
00:55:20.943 --> 00:55:23.237 line:82%
What would you like?
Should I get you milk or buttermilk?

590
00:55:23.237 --> 00:55:24.988 line:82%
Stop it now.

591
00:55:24.988 --> 00:55:28.492 line:82%
Come with me, dear.
He'll go on chattering till night.

592
00:55:28.492 --> 00:55:30.035 line:82%
-Come with me.
-Never mind...

593
00:55:30.035 --> 00:55:31.703 line:82%
-Excuse us.
-With pleasure.

594
00:55:34.373 --> 00:55:36.708 line:82%
-Hey, Veer! Where are you going?
-Well, I...

595
00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:38.460 line:82%
Wait a minute.

596
00:55:38.460 --> 00:55:40.712 line:82%
-Okay, get back to work, everyone!
-We're going.

597
00:55:40.712 --> 00:55:42.965 line:82%
-Yes. What happened?
-Wait...

598
00:55:42.965 --> 00:55:45.133 line:82%
Tell me.

599
00:55:45.133 --> 00:55:47.928 line:82%
Well, did you get
what I had asked you to?

600
00:55:47.928 --> 00:55:52.349 line:82%
Yes, here is your bottle of rum.

601
00:55:52.349 --> 00:55:53.934 line:82%
-But you can't drink alone.
-No, absolutely not.

602
00:55:53.934 --> 00:55:56.937 line:82%
Listen, if mom catches
you this time, I won't lie.

603
00:55:57.563 --> 00:56:00.107 line:82%
Just once... One last time.

604
00:56:01.275 --> 00:56:04.528 line:82%
-Okay, one last time.
-Go on. Go...

605
00:56:06.989 --> 00:56:08.949 line:82%
Cheers to the neighboring country!

606
00:56:19.418 --> 00:56:22.963 line:82%
-Let me do it.
-No, I'll manage.

607
00:56:22.963 --> 00:56:25.048 line:82%
The way you're doing it clearly shows

608
00:56:25.048 --> 00:56:27.384 line:82%
that someone else
does your hair at home.

609
00:56:27.384 --> 00:56:29.553 line:82%
Come, let me do it.

610
00:56:29.553 --> 00:56:32.806 line:82%
Consider this your home. Come.

611
00:56:34.433 --> 00:56:37.144 line:82%
-Is this Veer's room?
-Yes.

612
00:56:38.145 --> 00:56:42.649 line:82%
Whenever he brought a medal
or a picture, I'd put it up here.

613
00:56:43.942 --> 00:56:46.236 line:82%
And when he isn't at home

614
00:56:46.236 --> 00:56:49.448 line:82%
his father and I have
a look at his things here.

615
00:56:50.991 --> 00:56:52.826 line:82%
The three of you love each other a lot.

616
00:56:54.202 --> 00:56:57.831 line:82%
We have no one else
to share our love with.

617
00:56:57.831 --> 00:57:01.418 line:82%
He was very young
when his parents died.

618
00:57:01.418 --> 00:57:03.086 line:82%
Since then, it's just us.

619
00:57:03.879 --> 00:57:07.049 line:82%
We're actually his uncle and aunt

620
00:57:07.049 --> 00:57:10.594 line:82%
but he addresses us as his parents.

621
00:57:11.595 --> 00:57:14.848 line:82%
We don't have a child of our own.

622
00:57:14.848 --> 00:57:19.019 line:82%
It's just the three of us.

623
00:57:19.019 --> 00:57:22.314 line:82%
Hey! Here you go.
Your braid is done.

624
00:57:24.441 --> 00:57:27.361 line:82%
Wow! I look just like you guys.

625
00:57:27.361 --> 00:57:29.071 line:82%
This is nothing.

626
00:57:29.071 --> 00:57:31.657 line:82%
You'll look like
a true Punjabi at night.

627
00:57:31.657 --> 00:57:35.869 line:82%
Today is Lohri,
and we celebrate it on a grand scale.

628
00:57:35.869 --> 00:57:39.539 line:82%
I'll give you the dress
that I wore on my first Lohri.

629
00:57:39.539 --> 00:57:41.708 line:82%
No, ma'am. I'll wear my clothes...

630
00:57:41.708 --> 00:57:45.462 line:82%
Hey! Don't argue with me.

631
00:57:45.462 --> 00:57:48.006 line:82%
Look, you've come for just a day

632
00:57:48.006 --> 00:57:50.592 line:82%
and for this one day,
be one with us.

633
00:58:10.153 --> 00:58:12.072 line:82%
-Are you comfortable?
-Yes.

634
00:58:12.072 --> 00:58:14.241 line:82%
Let me tell you,
when I was young

635
00:58:14.866 --> 00:58:17.619 line:82%
I used to take my wife
to Amritsar on a bicycle just like that.

636
00:58:17.619 --> 00:58:19.621 line:82%
What do I tell you?

637
00:58:19.621 --> 00:58:22.040 line:82%
She's put on so much weight
now that she can't sit on the bicycle.

638
00:58:22.040 --> 00:58:24.960 line:82%
-But she's not that fat.
-I know better than you.

639
00:58:26.878 --> 00:58:30.966 line:82%
Veer was telling me that your wife
and you have built this village.

640
00:58:30.966 --> 00:58:35.053 line:82%
Yes. When we came here,
there were only farms.

641
00:58:35.595 --> 00:58:38.974 line:82%
Earlier, we'd write letters
to request electricity.

642
00:58:38.974 --> 00:58:41.685 line:82%
-Do you see this hospital?
-Yes.

643
00:58:41.685 --> 00:58:43.520 line:82%
There used to be
a cowshed here.

644
00:58:43.520 --> 00:58:44.855 line:82%
-How are you, Doctor?
-Hello.

645
00:58:44.855 --> 00:58:45.901 line:82%
Hello!

646
00:58:45.981 --> 00:58:47.858 line:82%
This is a school.

647
00:58:48.984 --> 00:58:53.822 line:82%
My wife and I were the first teachers.
No one was educated enough.

648
00:58:53.822 --> 00:58:56.825 line:82%
Now kids study through
the eighth grade here.

649
00:58:56.825 --> 00:59:02.205 line:82%
Later, we send the boys
to Kartarpur for further studies.

650
00:59:02.205 --> 00:59:06.376 line:82%
-What about the girls?
-How can we send the girls so far?

651
00:59:06.376 --> 00:59:09.296 line:82%
They have to stay back
and look after the household.

652
00:59:09.296 --> 00:59:12.257 line:82%
And anyway, what's the point of
getting them higher education?

653
00:59:12.257 --> 00:59:13.884 line:82%
That's unfair, sir.

654
00:59:17.345 --> 00:59:22.559 line:82%
-Unfair? How?
-Don't misunderstand me, sir.

655
00:59:22.559 --> 00:59:26.855 line:82%
What your wife and you have done
for this village is commendable.

656
00:59:26.855 --> 00:59:30.609 line:82%
You encouraged the
boys to fight the world.

657
00:59:30.609 --> 00:59:33.195 line:82%
But you made the girls weak.

658
00:59:33.779 --> 00:59:37.199 line:82%
That's why Veer is an Air Force pilot

659
00:59:37.199 --> 00:59:40.076 line:82%
but the girls in the village
remained illiterate.

660
00:59:41.495 --> 00:59:44.372 line:82%
Girls have reached great heights, sir.

661
00:59:44.372 --> 00:59:47.375 line:82%
They are equal to boys.

662
00:59:47.375 --> 00:59:50.879 line:82%
Who knows,
maybe after being educated

663
00:59:50.879 --> 00:59:52.923 line:82%
a girl from this village could have been
much more successful than Veer.

664
00:59:52.923 --> 00:59:55.050 line:82%
Don't you think?

665
00:59:55.050 --> 00:59:57.761 line:82%
