02:21:15.300 --> 02:21:20.097 line:82%
Everyone was killed. My name
was in the list of passengers too.

1551
02:21:22.307 --> 02:21:27.312 line:82%
I was glad that mom and dad
would get the news of my demise.

1552
02:21:29.690 --> 02:21:32.963 line:82%
If they had got the news
of me going missing

1553
02:21:33.153 --> 02:21:38.490 line:82%
they'd neither be able
to live, nor die in peace.

1554
02:21:39.074 --> 02:21:42.411 line:82%
In India, Veer Singh was dead.

1555
02:21:42.828 --> 02:21:46.957 line:82%
And there was no one
by the name of Veer Singh in Pakistan.

1556
02:21:50.001 --> 02:21:54.131 line:82%
He had just one identity now.

1557
02:21:56.133 --> 02:22:00.011 line:82%
Prisoner number 786.

1558
02:22:10.689 --> 02:22:15.819 line:82%
786...

1559
02:22:18.655 --> 02:22:22.033 line:82%
My country owes
you 22 years of your life.

1560
02:22:24.202 --> 02:22:27.247 line:82%
I can't get you those 22 years back.

1561
02:22:30.542 --> 02:22:33.295 line:82%
But I promise you.

1562
02:22:33.295 --> 02:22:36.131 line:82%
I won't offer flowers
on my father's coffin

1563
02:22:36.131 --> 02:22:38.592 line:82%
until Veer Pratap Singh
gets his name,

1564
02:22:38.592 --> 02:22:41.970 line:82%
identity and country back.

1565
02:23:06.703 --> 02:23:08.832 line:82%
So, Ms. Samya Siddique,
this is your first case.

1566
02:23:08.872 --> 02:23:09.940 line:82%
Yes.

1567
02:23:09.980 --> 02:23:11.708 line:82%
-Congratulations.
-Thank you, sir.

1568
02:23:11.708 --> 02:23:14.795 line:82%
And you're the defense council
on behalf of the Human Rights Commission.

1569
02:23:14.795 --> 02:23:17.839 line:82%
-That's right, sir.
-Good. That's good.

1570
02:23:17.839 --> 02:23:20.300 line:82%
There's no one from the prosecution yet.

1571
02:23:20.300 --> 02:23:22.844 line:82%
-Well, sir, he's on his way.
-May I come in, sir?

1572
02:23:23.386 --> 02:23:25.263 line:82%
Mr. Zakir, come in.

1573
02:23:26.598 --> 02:23:28.266 line:82%
-Good morning, sir.
-Good morning.

1574
02:23:28.266 --> 02:23:30.310 line:82%
-Please come.
-Thank you.

1575
02:23:30.769 --> 02:23:33.480 line:82%
-That's Mr. Zakir Ahmed.
-I know.

1576
02:23:34.689 --> 02:23:37.108 line:82%
I know him quite well.

1577
02:23:38.819 --> 02:23:40.028 line:82%
Please come.

1578
02:23:40.028 --> 02:23:42.989 line:82%
I'm sorry, Your Honor.
You're aware of the traffic in Lahore.

1579
02:23:43.990 --> 02:23:45.659 line:82%
Mr. Zakir,

1580
02:23:45.659 --> 02:23:48.787 line:82%
are you presenting this case on
be half of the Government of Pakistan?

1581
02:23:48.787 --> 02:23:51.832 line:82%
Yes. Actually, it's been a long time
since I came to court.

1582
02:23:52.123 --> 02:23:54.084 line:82%
People might think that Zakir Ahmed

1583
02:23:54.084 --> 02:23:55.836 line:82%
has forgotten how to fight a case.

1584
02:23:55.836 --> 02:23:58.630 line:82%
And anyway, this case seems interesting.

1585
02:23:58.630 --> 02:23:59.840 line:82%
What do you think, Samya?

1586
02:24:01.758 --> 02:24:06.304 line:82%
-Do you know each other?
-Yes.

1587
02:24:06.304 --> 02:24:09.683 line:82%
Samya used to work for me,

1588
02:24:09.683 --> 02:24:11.643 line:82%
but perhaps, she didn't
like the way I functioned and so,

1589
02:24:11.643 --> 02:24:14.187 line:82%
she joined the Human Rights camp.

1590
02:24:14.729 --> 02:24:19.526 line:82%
She's a talented lady.
It'll be fun to argue against her.

1591
02:24:21.778 --> 02:24:25.657 line:82%
Look, I had a special motive
behind calling you two here.

1592
02:24:27.158 --> 02:24:32.038 line:82%
I'd be better if both the parties
compromised outside the court.

1593
02:24:33.081 --> 02:24:35.834 line:82%
Or else, the date for the day
after tomorrow is fixed for the hearing.

1594
02:24:35.834 --> 02:24:39.296 line:82%
If the case doesn't
commence the day after tomorrow

1595
02:24:39.296 --> 02:24:42.173 line:82%
then you might have
to wait for another six months

1596
02:24:42.173 --> 02:24:43.675 line:82%
or even a year for the next hearing.

1597
02:24:43.675 --> 02:24:45.135 line:82%
We're ready, sir.

1598
02:24:45.135 --> 02:24:48.096 line:82%
-But if the defense lawyer needs time...
-I'm ready, sir.

1599
02:24:48.096 --> 02:24:49.931 line:82%
But Samya...

1600
02:24:49.931 --> 02:24:51.933 line:82%
Sir, let's have the hearing
the day after tomorrow.

1601
02:24:52.517 --> 02:24:56.146 line:82%
My client has been awaiting
justice for the past 22 years.

1602
02:24:56.146 --> 02:25:00.609 line:82%
-I can't make him wait anymore.
-Okay, then. That's fixed.

1603
02:25:02.444 --> 02:25:05.322 line:82%
Thank you for coming here.

1604
02:25:05.322 --> 02:25:07.157 line:82%
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

1605
02:25:10.035 --> 02:25:15.206 line:82%
Okay, Samya.
I'll see you in court. Good bye.

1606
02:25:21.504 --> 02:25:23.757 line:82%
This case seemed impossible
to win since the beginning.

1607
02:25:23.757 --> 02:25:26.509 line:82%
And now that Zakir Ahmed
is against us, we stand no chance.

1608
02:25:27.510 --> 02:25:31.306 line:82%
But this case is way below his standards.
Then, I wonder why...

1609
02:25:31.806 --> 02:25:33.892 line:82%
I just don't understand.

1610
02:25:33.892 --> 02:25:37.479 line:82%
Look, make some excuse and
withdraw yourself from this case.

1611
02:25:37.896 --> 02:25:39.648 line:82%
This is your first case.

1612
02:25:39.648 --> 02:25:43.193 line:82%
You know how Zakir Ahmed
humiliates his opposition.

1613
02:25:43.193 --> 02:25:47.113 line:82%
-He'll destroy your career.
-That's what he wants.

1614
02:25:47.113 --> 02:25:48.365 line:82%
What do you mean?

1615
02:25:48.365 --> 02:25:49.741 line:82%
Sahir, I'll tell you what.

1616
02:25:49.741 --> 02:25:52.118 line:82%
Go to the office and
prepare a list of the witnesses.

1617
02:25:52.118 --> 02:25:53.495 line:82%
I'll be right there.

1618
02:25:53.495 --> 02:25:55.538 line:82%
-But where are you going?
-To meet Zakir Ahmed.

1619
02:25:55.538 --> 02:25:59.042 line:82%
Okay... What! Samya...

1620
02:26:00.835 --> 02:26:03.421 line:82%
Ms. Samya Siddique.

1621
02:26:04.005 --> 02:26:08.593 line:82%
You had sworn to never again
step inside my office.

1622
02:26:08.593 --> 02:26:11.638 line:82%
How come you're here
to see my face today?

1623
02:26:11.638 --> 02:26:13.848 line:82%
It's nothing like that, sir.

1624
02:26:13.848 --> 02:26:17.560 line:82%
Our principles were different,
that's all.

1625
02:26:17.560 --> 02:26:21.564 line:82%
And I thought that if
I can't respect your principles

1626
02:26:21.564 --> 02:26:24.651 line:82%
then I should quit.

1627
02:26:24.651 --> 02:26:28.780 line:82%
Interesting. Very interesting.

1628
02:26:28.780 --> 02:26:31.449 line:82%
You have such great
principles at a very young age.

1629
02:26:31.449 --> 02:26:34.536 line:82%
I've inherited my
principles from my father, sir.

1630
02:26:35.829 --> 02:26:37.789 line:82%
Do you know, Samya?

1631
02:26:37.789 --> 02:26:42.961 line:82%
You're the first person to have
refused a case offered by Zakir Ahmed.

1632
02:26:42.961 --> 02:26:46.506 line:82%
People wait for several years
to have their first case.

1633
02:26:47.424 --> 02:26:51.678 line:82%
But I recognized your
talent and chose you.

1634
02:26:51.678 --> 02:26:53.722 line:82%
I didn't even consider
your age and experience,

1635
02:26:53.722 --> 02:26:57.267 line:82%
or even the fact that you're a woman.

1636
02:26:57.267 --> 02:27:01.229 line:82%
And what did you do in return?
You bluntly rejected that case.

1637
02:27:02.313 --> 02:27:05.191 line:82%
That case would
have freed a criminal, sir,

1638
02:27:05.650 --> 02:27:07.110 line:82%
and the way I saw it,
that was wrong.

1639
02:27:07.110 --> 02:27:10.113 line:82%
It's not the lawyer's job to think
about what's right and wrong!

1640
02:27:10.113 --> 02:27:11.656 line:82%
The court does that.

1641
02:27:11.656 --> 02:27:16.328 line:82%
A lawyer's job is to win the case,
no matter what! That's it!

1642
02:27:17.579 --> 02:27:20.415 line:82%
That's the difference
between you and me, sir.

1643
02:27:20.415 --> 02:27:25.378 line:82%
Your principle is to fight to win,
whereas I want to fight for the truth.

1644
02:27:25.378 --> 02:27:28.631 line:82%
Interesting. Very interesting.

1645
02:27:30.133 --> 02:27:33.219 line:82%
So, now,
you're going to teach me the law.

1646
02:27:33.219 --> 02:27:35.764 line:82%
This is all that was
left for me to experience.

1647
02:27:36.389 --> 02:27:42.687 line:82%
All right, forget it. The incidents of
the past will only freshen our wounds.

1648
02:27:42.687 --> 02:27:46.941 line:82%
Since you've come this far,
I'm sure it's something important.

1649
02:27:47.901 --> 02:27:51.988 line:82%
Have a seat.
Tell me, how may I help you?

1650
02:27:57.077 --> 02:28:00.955 line:82%
Sir, this is my first case.

1651
02:28:00.955 --> 02:28:03.958 line:82%
Obviously, I'm going to make mistakes.

1652
02:28:04.959 --> 02:28:08.421 line:82%
And it'll be even more difficult
for me if you're in the opposition.

1653
02:28:09.381 --> 02:28:12.884 line:82%
I don't want that Indian prisoner

1654
02:28:12.884 --> 02:28:15.678 line:82%
to be deprived of freedom
because of my mistakes.

1655
02:28:15.678 --> 02:28:19.974 line:82%
Because the truth is, he is innocent.

1656
02:28:19.974 --> 02:28:23.311 line:82%
Whatever happened
with him was unfair, sir.

1657
02:28:23.311 --> 02:28:26.481 line:82%
And he deserves freedom
in all senses.

1658
02:28:29.776 --> 02:28:33.238 line:82%
So, you've fallen
to my standards eventually.

1659
02:28:33.238 --> 02:28:37.617 line:82%
Basically, you're here to seek
help to win your first case, right?

1660
02:28:40.245 --> 02:28:44.582 line:82%
Defeating Zakir Ahmed will
escalate your career, right?

1661
02:28:45.375 --> 02:28:49.379 line:82%
Perhaps, you're forgetting
that Zakir Ahmed has never lost a case.

1662
02:28:49.379 --> 02:28:52.799 line:82%
And it's all the more
important for me to win this case.

1663
02:28:52.799 --> 02:28:57.345 line:82%
Because I want to teach
a lesson to people like you

1664
02:28:57.345 --> 02:29:02.308 line:82%
for refusing to follow the principles
of Zakir Ahmed.

1665
02:29:05.478 --> 02:29:08.148 line:82%
What happened, Ms. Samya Siddique?

1666
02:29:08.148 --> 02:29:11.317 line:82%
Don't you believe in the
principles of truth anymore?

1667
02:29:11.317 --> 02:29:13.653 line:82%
Why have you come
here to beg for your win?

1668
02:29:14.654 --> 02:29:18.783 line:82%
I'm sorry, sir.
I mistook you for a human being.

1669
02:29:20.577 --> 02:29:24.414 line:82%
I only came to discuss if there is a way

1670
02:29:24.414 --> 02:29:29.294 line:82%
to resolve this outside
of court to get this man freedom.

1671
02:29:29.294 --> 02:29:32.672 line:82%
But you consider my
humanity as my weakness.

1672
02:29:34.966 --> 02:29:39.762 line:82%
Now I'll see you in court, sir.
Be prepared to face your first defeat.

1673
02:29:40.972 --> 02:29:46.477 line:82%
Because now, even the government
of Pakistan cannot stop me

1674
02:29:46.477 --> 02:29:48.688 line:82%
from sending prisoner number
786 back to India, let alone you.

1675
02:29:54.861 --> 02:29:58.072 line:82%
Interesting. Very interesting.

1676
02:30:03.494 --> 02:30:05.872 line:82%
May I ask you something?

1677
02:30:06.915 --> 02:30:10.335 line:82%
You didn't talk to anyone
all these years.

1678
02:30:10.335 --> 02:30:12.545 line:82%
Then why did you tell me your story?

1679
02:30:17.300 --> 02:30:21.012 line:82%
You called me by my name.

1680
02:30:22.138 --> 02:30:24.015 line:82%
What?

1681
02:30:24.724 --> 02:30:30.104 line:82%
You're the first person
who thought I was innocent.

1682
02:30:30.104 --> 02:30:35.526 line:82%
You're the first person
who believed that I'm Veer Singh.

1683
02:30:39.697 --> 02:30:45.578 line:82%
The truth is, in all these years,
I had forgotten who I am.

1684
02:30:48.373 --> 02:30:52.502 line:82%
You reminded me of my identity.

1685
02:30:53.378 --> 02:30:56.339 line:82%
You called me by my
name and gave me respect.

1686
02:30:57.257 --> 02:31:01.803 line:82%
Veer. Veer Pratap Singh.

1687
02:31:06.975 --> 02:31:09.978 line:82%
22 years...

1688
02:31:09.978 --> 02:31:14.399 line:82%
For a prisoner who's been
humiliated for the past 22 years

1689
02:31:15.400 --> 02:31:19.904 line:82%
this was a great deal.
A great deal.

1690
02:31:29.247 --> 02:31:32.709 line:82%
I'm going to eat more.

1691
02:31:38.548 --> 02:31:40.425 line:82%
Tomorrow's our
first hearing in the court.

1692
02:31:40.425 --> 02:31:42.302 line:82%
I hope you remember your promise.

1693
02:31:43.428 --> 02:31:45.888 line:82%
You have to change your
appearance from prisoner number 786

1694
02:31:45.888 --> 02:31:48.516 line:82%
and come as
Squadron Leader Veer Pratap Singh.

1695
02:31:50.282 --> 02:31:53.521 line:82%
-No.
-What?

1696
02:31:53.980 --> 02:31:55.481 line:82%
Do you remember your promise?

1697
02:31:55.481 --> 02:32:01.279 line:82%
Absolutely. Zaara or the Hayat Khan
family won't be mentioned in court.

1698
02:32:01.279 --> 02:32:06.326 line:82%
You stay true to your promise,
and I'll fulfill mine.

1699
02:32:35.521 --> 02:32:40.360 line:82%
Your Honor, the defense would
like to call its first witness.

1700
02:32:44.155 --> 02:32:47.283 line:82%
The defense calls its first witness.

1701
02:32:49.577 --> 02:32:51.996 line:82%
The defense rests, Your Honor.

1702
02:33:54.851 --> 02:33:58.229 line:82%
The prosecution is
permitted to present their case.

1703
02:34:00.898 --> 02:34:02.650 line:82%
Your Honor,

1704
02:34:03.317 --> 02:34:08.281 line:82%
a person was confined
in prison for the past 22 years.

1705
02:34:09.782 --> 02:34:13.578 line:82%
That prison is in Pakistan.

1706
02:34:14.620 --> 02:34:20.460 line:82%
And the person who's been imprisoned in
a Pakistani prison for the past 22 years

1707
02:34:20.460 --> 02:34:24.088 line:82%
is an Indian.

1708
02:34:25.256 --> 02:34:30.178 line:82%
On hearing this, you, I

1709
02:34:30.178 --> 02:34:34.098 line:82%
and the people
here might get a bit emotional.

1710
02:34:35.099 --> 02:34:40.521 line:82%
We'd want this person to return
to his country somehow.

1711
02:34:41.647 --> 02:34:43.900 line:82%
We'd like him to go home.

1712
02:34:43.900 --> 02:34:45.485 line:82%
Because we're humans.

1713
02:34:46.110 --> 02:34:49.322 line:82%
And we've been taught to value humans.

1714
02:34:50.615 --> 02:34:52.617 line:82%
But, Your Honor,

1715
02:34:53.075 --> 02:34:58.331 line:82%
what humans can't analyze
in court, the law does.

1716
02:34:58.331 --> 02:35:01.834 line:82%
And for the law,
a country is greater than any human.

1717
02:35:01.834 --> 02:35:04.879 line:82%
And the person who
works against a country

1718
02:35:04.879 --> 02:35:08.049 line:82%
deserves not just 22 years
of imprisonment, but the death penalty!

1719
02:35:15.806 --> 02:35:19.227 line:82%
This case is absolutely transparent,
Your Honor.

1720
02:35:19.227 --> 02:35:22.063 line:82%
There's no scope for doubt in this case.

1721
02:35:22.438 --> 02:35:24.440 line:82%
The prosecution
will prove in 30 minutes,

1722
02:35:24.440 --> 02:35:27.818 line:82%
with the help
of only three witnesses

1723
02:35:27.818 --> 02:35:32.949 line:82%
that the accused Rajesh Rathore does
not deserve to go back to his country.

1724
02:35:34.242 --> 02:35:35.743 line:82%
That's all, Your Honor.

1725
02:35:37.119 --> 02:35:40.373 line:82%
I now permit the defense
to present their case.

1726
02:35:43.167 --> 02:35:46.212 line:82%
Ms. Siddique, best of luck.

1727
02:36:14.824 --> 02:36:19.203 line:82%
Your Honor, the prosecution council,
Mr. Zahir Khan, easily...

1728
02:36:19.203 --> 02:36:20.371 line:82%
Zakir Ahmed.

1729
02:36:20.371 --> 02:36:23.583 line:82%
He easily said that this case
is absolutely transparent.

1730
02:36:23.583 --> 02:36:25.167 line:82%
But Mr. Zahir Khan has forgotten...

1731
02:36:25.167 --> 02:36:27.420 line:82%
Samya Siddique,
my name is Zakir Ahmed.

1732
02:36:27.420 --> 02:36:30.798 line:82%
You got furious on being
called by the wrong name just once.

1733
02:36:30.798 --> 02:36:32.049 line:82%
Just imagine!

1734
02:36:32.049 --> 02:36:34.885 line:82%
What would you go
through if people called you

1735
02:36:34.885 --> 02:36:36.429 line:82%
by the wrong name for 22 years?

1736
02:36:41.058 --> 02:36:47.106 line:82%
Your Honor, this case isn't being
fought only to send an Indian back home.

1737
02:36:47.565 --> 02:36:52.445 line:82%
This case is being fought
to get a person his identity back.

1738
02:36:53.070 --> 02:36:56.324 line:82%
A man is asking for
his name back, Your Honor.

1739
02:36:56.616 --> 02:37:00.494 line:82%
He says he is Veer Pratap Singh.

1740
02:37:00.995 --> 02:37:04.749 line:82%
Ex-Indian Air Force Officer,
Squadron Leader Veer Pratap Singh.

1741
02:37:06.626 --> 02:37:09.879 line:82%
All he wants is his name back,

1742
02:37:09.879 --> 02:37:12.298 line:82%
with respect. That's it.

1743
02:37:12.298 --> 02:37:16.802 line:82%
Your Honor, I may need more than 30
minutes, unlike the prosecution council

1744
02:37:16.802 --> 02:37:22.183 line:82%
but I will prove that he is
Veer Pratap Singh, not Rajesh Rathore.

1745
02:37:22.183 --> 02:37:27.480 line:82%
Then, whether you send him to India
or keep him in Pakistan is your decision.

1746
02:37:27.480 --> 02:37:29.732 line:82%
That's all, Your Honor.

1747
02:37:30.358 --> 02:37:33.027 line:82%
The prosecution may
now present his witnesses.

1748
02:37:33.027 --> 02:37:37.073 line:82%
Your Honor,
I'd like to call upon my first witness,

1749
02:37:37.073 --> 02:37:39.367 line:82%
Police Inspector Dilbaaz Khan.

1750
02:37:39.367 --> 02:37:44.538 line:82%
22 years ago, he was the one
who arrested Rajesh Rathore.

1751
02:37:44.538 --> 02:37:47.375 line:82%
Dilbaaz Khan be summoned.

1752
02:37:47.375 --> 02:37:49.377 line:82%
Can you tell the court

1753
02:37:49.377 --> 02:37:53.839 line:82%
without any hesitations
as to who this man is?

1754
02:37:53.839 --> 02:37:56.509 line:82%
Yes, I remember clearly.

1755
02:37:56.509 --> 02:38:00.680 line:82%
This man is a spy from India,
a RAW agent, Rajesh Rathore.

1756
02:38:01.597 --> 02:38:04.809 line:82%
Around 22 years ago,
Anwar Ali and I

1757
02:38:04.809 --> 02:38:08.229 line:82%
made him get off the bus heading
to India from Lahore, and arrested him.

1758
02:38:09.105 --> 02:38:11.315 line:82%
We had information
